absint "MAY 2013" WordPress Codex "Function Reference"
======================================================

NAME
----

absint - Converts a value to a non-negative integer.

SYNOPSIS
--------

Converts a value to a non-negative integer.

Synonym of abs ( intval ( \$foo ) ).

USAGE
-----

` <?php absint( $maybeint ); ?> `

PARAMETERS
----------

 `$maybeint` 
:   ([*mixed*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Mixed "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) Data you wish to have converted to a non-negative
    integer.
    Default: *None*

RETURN VALUES
-------------

 `` `(int)`{style="color:gray"} 
:   A non-negative integer.

CHANGE LOG
----------

Since: [2.5](/Version_2.5 "Version 2.5")

SOURCE FILE
-----------

`absint()` is located in `wp-includes/functions.php`

Retrieved from
"[http://codex.wordpress.org/Function\_Reference/absint](http://codex.wordpress.org/Function_Reference/absint)"

